net.roydesign.mac
Interface MRJFolderConstants

All Known Implementing Classes:
MRJAdapter
public interface MRJFolderConstants

This interface defines some useful Mac OS constants to use with the MRJAdapter.findFolder() method.

Version:
MRJ Adapter 1.2

kChewableItemsFolderType

static final int kChewableItemsFolderType
The invisible folder on the system disk called “Cleanup at Startup” whose contents are deleted when the system is restarted, instead of merely being moved to the Trash. When the findFolder() method indicates this folder is available (by returning a non-null value), developers should usually use this folder for their temporary items, in preference to the Temporary Folder. Supported with Mac OS 8 and later.

See Also:

kApplicationSupportFolderType

static final int kApplicationSupportFolderType
The Application Support folder in the System Folder. This folder contains code and data files needed by third-party applications. These files should usually not be written to after they are installed. In general, files deleted from this folder remove functionality from an application, unlike files in the Preferences folder, which should be non-essential. One type of file that could be placed here would be plug-ins that the user might want to maintain separately from any application, such as for an image-processing application that has many “fourth-party” plug-ins that the user might want to upgrade separately from the host application. Another type of file that might belong in this folder would be application-specific data files that are not preferences, such as for a scanner application that needs to read description files for specific scanner models according to which are currently available on the SCSI bus or network. Supported with Mac OS 8 and later.

kFavoritesFolderType

static final int kFavoritesFolderType
The Favorites folder in the System Folder. This folder is for storing Internet location files, aliases, and aliases to other frequently used items. Facilities for adding items into this folder are found in Contextual Menus, the Finder, Navigation Services, and others. Supported with Mac OS 8.1 and later.
